OTHER MOSAICS in same sampling field

Florida garfish: Collin S.P and Northcutt, R.G. (1993) Brain Behav Evol 42: 295-320

Re-digitized from the original authors' printed Figs: see general Excel catalogue for NND, auto- and crosscorrelogram data implying that both mosaics show subsets of a single natural RGC type; NOTE that the scaling of X,Y is non-standard and that relative spatial values (ER and NND) are more exact than absolute values. Absolute values rely on the precision to which the published scale bar could be measured; this probably accounts for a ~1% difference between the authors' mean NNDs and ours.
